prompt:
Add a public function called SafeIncrement to Contracts.calr that increments a positive number. Use implication in the postcondition to express that if x > 0, then result > x.

Use this exact Calor implication syntax:
§F{f001:SafeIncrement:pub}
  §I{i32:x}
  §O{i32}
  §S (-> (> x 0) (> result x))
  §R (+ x 1)
§/F{f001}

The (-> antecedent consequent) syntax expresses implication:
- Reads as: if antecedent then consequent
- The contract only constrains when the antecedent is true
- Useful for conditional postconditions
